WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.615
DroidProxy starts with a simple constraint.

00:00:02.615 --> 00:00:05.230
Factory Droids are strongest when they

00:00:05.230 --> 00:00:08.282
can use the models you already trust.

00:00:08.282 --> 00:00:10.897
But many teams already pay for

00:00:10.897 --> 00:00:14.385
Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini, or Kimi through subscription products.

00:00:14.385 --> 00:00:17.000
DroidProxy bridges that gap with a

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:18.744
small native Mac app.

00:00:18.744 --> 00:00:21.359
It lives in the menu bar,

00:00:21.359 --> 00:00:23.975
signs in through normal OAuth flows,

00:00:23.975 --> 00:00:26.590
and registers those accounts as custom

00:00:26.590 --> 00:00:27.898
models in Factory.

00:00:27.898 --> 00:00:29.642
The result is simple.

00:00:29.642 --> 00:00:30.949
Same Droid workflow.

00:00:30.949 --> 00:00:32.693
Your existing provider plans.

00:00:32.693 --> 00:00:34.873
No API keys to copy.

00:00:34.873 --> 00:00:37.052
No billing switch to rewire.

00:00:37.052 --> 00:00:40.539
At the center is a two-server local design.

00:00:40.539 --> 00:00:43.155
Droid CLI sends requests to ThinkingProxy

00:00:43.155 --> 00:00:46.206
on localhost port eight three one seven.

00:00:46.206 --> 00:00:48.822
ThinkingProxy is a thin Swift proxy

00:00:48.822 --> 00:00:50.565
built on Network framework.

00:00:50.565 --> 00:00:53.181
It forwards to a bundled CLIProxyAPI

00:00:53.181 --> 00:00:56.232
process on port eight three one eight.

00:00:56.232 --> 00:00:59.720
That backend owns provider OAuth and upstream calls.

00:00:59.720 --> 00:01:02.335
Both servers stay on loopback, so

00:01:02.335 --> 00:01:04.951
credentials and requests remain local until

00:01:04.951 --> 00:01:07.566
the provider call leaves your Mac.

00:01:07.566 --> 00:01:10.182
The settings window is where setup

00:01:10.182 --> 00:01:11.489
becomes one click.

00:01:11.489 --> 00:01:14.105
You connect Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini, and

00:01:14.105 --> 00:01:16.284
Kimi with normal browser login.

00:01:16.284 --> 00:01:18.900
DroidProxy watches the auth directory for

00:01:18.900 --> 00:01:21.515
credential changes, expiration, and disabled accounts.

00:01:21.515 --> 00:01:24.131
It also shows live Claude and

00:01:24.131 --> 00:01:26.746
Codex quota windows, so you can

00:01:26.746 --> 00:01:29.362
see what your subscription budget is

00:01:29.362 --> 00:01:31.541
doing before a long session.

00:01:31.541 --> 00:01:34.157
Once accounts are connected, the Apply

00:01:34.157 --> 00:01:36.336
button writes Factory custom models.

00:01:36.336 --> 00:01:38.952
The model catalog is source controlled

00:01:38.952 --> 00:01:40.696
in DroidProxyModelCatalog dot swift.

00:01:40.696 --> 00:01:43.311
Each entry includes provider routing, max

00:01:43.311 --> 00:01:45.927
output tokens, and native reasoning metadata.

00:01:45.927 --> 00:01:48.542
That lets Droid CLI expose reasoning

00:01:48.542 --> 00:01:49.850
choices per session.

00:01:49.850 --> 00:01:52.465
DroidProxy does not fake or inject

00:01:52.465 --> 00:01:53.773
those reasoning levels.

00:01:53.773 --> 00:01:56.388
It registers the supported levels, then

00:01:56.388 --> 00:01:58.568
forwards the request body unchanged.

00:01:58.568 --> 00:02:01.183
The request path is intentionally narrow.

00:02:01.183 --> 00:02:03.799
For Claude thinking requests, DroidProxy adjusts

00:02:03.799 --> 00:02:06.850
beta headers so visible thinking blocks work.

00:02:06.850 --> 00:02:09.466
For GPT Fast Mode, it adds

00:02:09.466 --> 00:02:12.081
service tier priority when the user

00:02:12.081 --> 00:02:13.389
toggles it on.

00:02:13.389 --> 00:02:16.005
For Gemini Code Assist models, it

00:02:16.005 --> 00:02:18.620
rewrites Responses API paths to the

00:02:18.620 --> 00:02:21.236
chat completions path the backend supports.

00:02:21.236 --> 00:02:23.851
Everything else passes through with key

00:02:23.851 --> 00:02:26.902
order preserved, which protects prompt cache behavior.

00:02:26.902 --> 00:02:30.390
The app shell keeps the moving parts predictable.

00:02:30.390 --> 00:02:33.005
AppDelegate starts the menu bar item,

00:02:33.005 --> 00:02:35.621
launches ThinkingProxy first, waits for it

00:02:35.621 --> 00:02:38.236
to listen, then starts the backend.

00:02:38.236 --> 00:02:40.852
ServerManager owns the child process, merged

00:02:40.852 --> 00:02:43.467
config, login commands, and cleanup for

00:02:43.467 --> 00:02:44.775
orphaned backend processes.

00:02:44.775 --> 00:02:47.390
AuthManager reads the provider files from

00:02:47.390 --> 00:02:50.006
dot cli proxy api and enforces

00:02:50.006 --> 00:02:52.621
safety rules like keeping one enabled

00:02:52.621 --> 00:02:53.929
account per provider.

00:02:53.929 --> 00:02:56.545
For contributors, the hotspots are clear.

00:02:56.545 --> 00:02:59.160
SettingsView carries the SwiftUI control surface.

00:02:59.160 --> 00:03:01.775
ThinkingProxy carries request parsing, routing, and

00:03:01.775 --> 00:03:03.083
JSON insertion helpers.

00:03:03.083 --> 00:03:06.135
ServerManager carries backend lifecycle and provider enablement.

00:03:06.135 --> 00:03:08.750
The React website is small, separate,

00:03:08.750 --> 00:03:11.801
and only markets the signed app bundle.

00:03:11.801 --> 00:03:14.853
That separation keeps the product path focused.

00:03:14.853 --> 00:03:18.340
The user downloads a notarized Apple Silicon app.

00:03:18.340 --> 00:03:20.084
They sign in once.

00:03:20.084 --> 00:03:21.392
They click Apply.

00:03:21.392 --> 00:03:24.007
Factory gets a catalog of custom

00:03:24.007 --> 00:03:26.187
models that route to localhost.

00:03:26.187 --> 00:03:29.238
Droid gets the model selector it expects.

00:03:29.238 --> 00:03:32.289
The upstream providers see normal authenticated requests.

00:03:32.289 --> 00:03:34.905
You can remember DroidProxy as a

00:03:34.905 --> 00:03:37.520
local adapter, not a new provider.

00:03:37.520 --> 00:03:40.136
It supervises OAuth, registers models, and

00:03:40.136 --> 00:03:42.751
smooths over a few protocol differences.

00:03:42.751 --> 00:03:46.239
It does not take ownership of reasoning policy.

00:03:46.239 --> 00:03:48.854
It does not expose a remote

00:03:48.854 --> 00:03:50.162
backend by default.

00:03:50.162 --> 00:03:52.777
It keeps the control plane in

00:03:52.777 --> 00:03:55.393
a native Mac app and the

00:03:55.393 --> 00:03:57.136
data path on localhost.

00:03:57.136 --> 00:04:00.624
That is why it fits neatly beside Factory.

00:04:00.624 --> 00:04:03.239
It makes existing subscriptions usable inside

00:04:03.239 --> 00:04:05.855
Droids while keeping the workflow familiar,

00:04:05.855 --> 00:04:07.163
local, and transparent.
